# efc65bae01054906b8b2d4a8e1444347
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:2
msgid "Counting Number of Vertices in a Layer"
msgstr "Counting Number of Vertices in a Layer"

# c04ea03b4d5c41029d0b558e7a5297dc
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:8
msgid ""
"QGIS doesn’t have a built-in function to calculate number of vertices for "
"each feature in a layer. But a very handy plugin called **Vertices Counter**"
" fills this gap and adds a few handy features as well."
msgstr "QGIS doesn’t have a built-in function to calculate number of vertices for each feature in a layer. But a very handy plugin called **Vertices Counter** fills this gap and adds a few handy features as well."

# 45284ac075a146628eefbaa1be329826
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:13
msgid "Procedure"
msgstr "Procedure"

# 0d56d7977d964edf99cb37764052cfa5
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:15
msgid ""
"Find and install the **Vertices Counter** plugin. See :doc:`using_plugins` "
"for details on installing plugins in QGIS."
msgstr "Find and install the **Vertices Counter** plugin. See :doc:`using_plugins` for details on installing plugins in QGIS."

# 7f6e6133e02941b2a0f22b0b5db97f85
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:21
msgid ""
"Load any polygon or line layer in QGIS. Go to :menuselection:`Vector --> "
"Vertices Counter --> Vertices Counter`."
msgstr "Load any polygon or line layer in QGIS. Go to :menuselection:`Vector --> Vertices Counter --> Vertices Counter`."

# c3f30a2518d04923abe3839623c09ff8
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:27
msgid ""
"By default, the active layer will be selected under the :guilabel:`Layer "
"Selection`. You may select any other loaded layers or open layer directly "
"from disk as well. The plugin has an option called :guilabel:`Create new "
"column` which can add an number of vertices as an attribute for each "
"feature. This is handy for a lot of use cases, so we can select that option."
" Now click on the :guilabel:`Count Vertices` button and the "
":guilabel:`Results` section will be populated with vertex count for each "
"feature. You can even see the :guilabel:`Total Vertices` displayed on the "
"side."
msgstr "By default, the active layer will be selected under the :guilabel:`Layer Selection`. You may select any other loaded layers or open layer directly from disk as well. The plugin has an option called :guilabel:`Create new column` which can add an number of vertices as an attribute for each feature. This is handy for a lot of use cases, so we can select that option. Now click on the :guilabel:`Count Vertices` button and the :guilabel:`Results` section will be populated with vertex count for each feature. You can even see the :guilabel:`Total Vertices` displayed on the side."

# c88d4cec94c14a53a9e4de40574a9331
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:40
msgid ""
"Back in the main QGIS window, let's verify if a new column was added to our "
"layer. Right-click the layer and select :guilabel:`Open Attribute Table`."
msgstr "Back in the main QGIS window, let's verify if a new column was added to our layer. Right-click the layer and select :guilabel:`Open Attribute Table`."

# afb9898fca1f4061ba755089a686fe9a
#: ../../source/docs/counting_vertices.rst:46
msgid ""
"As you will notice, a column named *Vertices* will be added at the end with "
"values representing the vertex count for each feature. This column can come "
"in handy if you want to do a query such as *Select all features with "
"Vertices > X*."
msgstr "As you will notice, a column named *Vertices* will be added at the end with values representing the vertex count for each feature. This column can come in handy if you want to do a query such as *Select all features with Vertices > X*."
